A truck driver will on Monday be arraigned at a Thika Court to be charged with causing the death of two persons by careless driving. Samson Oyodi Morrias was arrested for causing the deaths on Thursday afternoon near Gretsa University on the Thika-Garissa Highway. According to Thika West OCPD Willy Simba, Oyodi was driving a trailer towards Makongeni when he hit a motorcyclist from behind, killing him on the spot. A female pillion passenger was rushed to Thika Level Five Hospital but she succumbed to her injuries. The bodies of the victims have been preserved at General Kago Road Funeral Home awaiting identification by relatives. The truck and the motorcycle wreckage from are detained at Thika Police Station where the suspect is being held. Click here for the latest political news 